    difficulty: "core",
    prompt: "Implement `top_p_filter(probs, p)`.\n\n`probs` is a 1-D numpy array of token probabilities (non-negative; may not sum exactly to 1 — **renormalize first**). Keep the **smallest set of highest-probability tokens** whose cumulative probability is **>= p**, zero out everything else, and renormalize the kept probabilities to sum to 1.\n\nReturn a numpy array of the same shape. The kept set must always contain **at least one token** (the argmax), and positions must stay aligned with the input (do not sort the output).",
    starter: "import numpy as np\n\ndef top_p_filter(probs, p):\n    # TODO: renormalize, keep the nucleus, zero the rest, renormalize the kept mass.\n    raise NotImplementedError\n",
    solution: "import numpy as np\n\ndef top_p_filter(probs, p):\n    probs = np.asarray(probs, dtype=float)\n    probs = probs / probs.sum()\n    order = np.argsort(-probs, kind='stable')\n    csum = np.cumsum(probs[order])\n    # smallest k with cumulative >= p (at least 1)\n    k = int(np.searchsorted(csum, p) + 1)\n    k = max(1, min(k, len(probs)))\n    keep = order[:k]\n    out = np.zeros_like(probs)\n    out[keep] = probs[keep]\n    return out / out.sum()\n",
