    prompt: "Implement class `PrefixCache(max_entries)` — prompt caching keyed by token prefixes.\n\n- `put(prefix, state)` — cache computed KV `state` for a token `prefix` (a tuple). Re-putting an existing prefix updates state + recency.\n- `get_longest(tokens)` — return `(matched_len, state)` for the **longest cached prefix** of `tokens`, or `(0, None)`. A hit **refreshes recency** (LRU).\n- Over `max_entries`, evict the least-recently-used entry.",
    starter: "class PrefixCache:\n    def __init__(self, max_entries):\n        # TODO: dict of prefix-tuple -> state + LRU order.\n        raise NotImplementedError\n\n    def put(self, prefix, state):\n        raise NotImplementedError\n\n    def get_longest(self, tokens):\n        raise NotImplementedError\n",
    solution: "from collections import OrderedDict\n\nclass PrefixCache:\n    def __init__(self, max_entries):\n        self.max_entries = max_entries\n        self._d = OrderedDict()\n\n    def put(self, prefix, state):\n        key = tuple(prefix)\n        if key in self._d:\n            self._d.pop(key)\n        self._d[key] = state\n        while len(self._d) > self.max_entries:\n            self._d.popitem(last=False)\n\n    def get_longest(self, tokens):\n        toks = tuple(tokens)\n        best = None\n        for key in self._d:\n            if len(key) <= len(toks) and toks[:len(key)] == key:\n                if best is None or len(key) > len(best):\n                    best = key\n        if best is None:\n            return (0, None)\n        state = self._d.pop(best)\n        self._d[best] = state  # refresh recency\n        return (len(best), state)\n",
